Find H-Index

What is citations?
A citation means:

How many times other people referred to (used or mentioned) your research paper in their own research.

Imagine:

You wrote a research paper.

If:5 people use your paper in their research

Then your paper has 5 citations; citations[i] = number of times paper i was referenced by others
H-index tries to measure:“How many strong papers does a researcher have?”

class Solution {
    public int hIndex(int[] citations) {
        Arrays.sort(citations);
        
        int count = 0;
        int n = citations.length;
        
        for(int i = n - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
            if(citations[i] > count) {
                count++;
            } else {
                break;
            }
        }
        
        return count;
    }
}



